<% content_for :title, "About MRDBID" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Learn what MRDBID is, who built it, and how it supports mushroom observation, identification, and mycology collaboration." %>

<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">About MRDBID</h1>

  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
    MRDBID (MushRoom DataBase IDentification) is a mycology-focused project for documenting mushroom specimens,
    recording observation characters, and improving practical identification workflows over time.
  </p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
    The site combines a specimen notebook, character-entry tools, image support, reference content, and searchable
    datasets. The goal is to make mushroom documentation more structured, easier to review, and easier to share.
  </p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
    Public pages are intended for education and field documentation support. Logged-in features provide additional
    tools for creating and maintaining records.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">Editorial Approach</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
    MRDBID includes original notes and articles from active field use. Where outside references are used, they are
    cited to support consistency, transparency, and ongoing improvement of terminology and methods.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">Contact</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700">
    Questions or feedback: <%= link_to "Contact page", contact_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:underline" %>
  </p>
</div>
